- Fixed a bug where Fleet's stored Recovery Lock password state could become desynchronized from the managed macOS device. Apple removes the Recovery Lock password from the device when the MDM profile is removed, but Fleet previously continued to show the old password as verified. Fleet now soft-deletes the stored password whenever MDM is turned off for the host — whether by re-enrollment, by the device sending a CheckOut, by an admin unenrolling via the API, or by an osquery refetch reporting that the device is no longer enrolled in MDM. The recovery lock cron then enqueues a fresh SetRecoveryLock if the host re-enrolls. This also unsticks hosts whose initial SetRecoveryLock command was abandoned when the device re-authenticated before acknowledging it.
